African swine fever, Tanzania
-----------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 11 Feb 2011 from Dr WCH Mleche,
Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Livestock Development, Dar
Es Salaam, Tanzania

Summary
Report type: follow-up report no. 1
Start date: 3 Dec 2010
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 6 Dec 2010
Report date: 11 Feb 2011
Date submitted to OIE: 11 Feb 2011
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: April 2004
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country
Related reports
Immediate notification (8 Dec 2010)

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Katumba, Rungwe, Mbeya
Date of start of the outbreak: 6 Feb 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
